parameters:
"(It's strange to see people gathering in a facility that's
supposed to be sealed and unused   )"

"(Tina doesn't seem to be here, but   could this be a
jackpot?)"
"(There are several men   and that woman   could it be?)"

"   I should have completely erased my presence with my
unique skill, but...?"

"Ah, my technique is a bit special, you see. It can be
executed without being caught by your skills."

"(   I don't know the logic behind it, but it seems like
they've broken through Tina's Full Body as well.)"

"   When I caught you before, you weren't using such
techniques, were you?"
Selphie recognized the woman in front of her.

Bellra. She was the head of the human trafficking
organization that Selphie had captured before.

Suelle and Tina had heard the story from Selphie, but it was
Selphie who had actually faced and captured her.
"(How did she escape from prison   No, more importantly...)"

"(No, I mustn't rush   . Even if I decide to fight, her
abilities are too much of an unknown.)"
Selphie calmly assessed the situation around her.

"(There's only one exit in this room, the way I came in
but people are starting to gather.)"

Using her enemy detection skill, Selphie accurately grasped
the movements of the approaching enemies.

"(They're planning to surround me completely   but with this
much, I can!!)"
"You think you can escape, don't you?"

Just as she was about to move, Selphie was thrown off by
words that seemed to see right through her, causing her to
involuntarily stop in her tracks.
"Hey? How about we make a deal?"

"Yes, a very good proposal that I'm sure we'll both agree
on."

Bellra took out a device that looked like a tablet and
showed its screen to Selphie.
"Look? Do you recognize who's on this screen?"
The tablet displayed an image showing Suelle and Rise.

"These kids, huh? They're currently at Maroges' mansion.
What you're seeing is live footage."

"It's bad, isn't it? Trespassing like that   . They need to
be punished, don't they?"
"   Are you trying to threaten me?"
Upon seeing the footage, Selphie glared sharply at Bellra.

"   Even if you try something, it's useless as long as Rise
is there."
Yes, the footage showed not only Suelle but also Rise.

Even if Suelle, who was not good at fighting, was alone, as
long as Rise was there, they could handle being attacked.

"Is that so? But Rise-chan is such a good listener, isn't
she?"
Bellra took out a small microphone.
"Rise-chan. Could you raise your right hand for me?"

When Bellra gave instructions into the microphone, Rise, as
shown on the screen, raised her hand as directed.

"What do you think would happen if I ordered her right now
to eliminate Suelle, was it? This boy."

Bellra spoke with a sinister smile, seemingly enjoying the
situation.

"It's tragic, isn't it? Having to kill a comrade with her
own hands. Ah, Rise-chan might even cry."

"What have I done, you ask? Hehe, it's a contract of
servitude. I've made her into a brainwashed slave."

"Though, Rise-chan has probably forgotten that she's been
brainwashed."
Anger welled up inside Selphie upon hearing Bellra's words.

However, seeing Bellra respond so calmly as if it were a
normal conversation, Selphie realized that if she couldn't
use this to her advantage, Bellra might truly give Rise an
order, making it risky to act carelessly.

"Oh, scary. But you know, I only made the contract of
servitude. It was another man who actually did the
brainwashing."
"Hehe, she was tormented thoroughly and for a long time."
Bellra spoke slowly about Rise, as if to provoke Selphie.

"So, about this contract of servitude... I was thinking of
having you, Selphie-chan, enter into one as well."

"Of course, I'll present a benefit to you. If you agree to
the contract quietly, we won't lay a hand on Suelle here."
Bellra made the proposal as if offering a deal.
"Do you really think I can trust that?"

It was only natural. No one could trust the words of someone
who takes comrades as hostages just from listening to them.
"Don't worry, this is a contract after all."

"Have you ever heard of ancient spell formulas? They're
different from modern magic, used in the old times."

"A contract of servitude is something that binds slaves for
the purpose of achieving a goal, or it's a conditional
contract that forces criminals to work until they are
rehabilitated."

"And as a byproduct, if during the contract you completely
break their spirit and brainwash them, the hypnotic
brainwashing continues even after the contract is
terminated."

"So, if the brainwashing isn't complete and we unilaterally
break the contract..."

"The contract is immediately nullified and Selphie-chan
becomes free. We would then be overpowered by you."

In other words, not laying a hand on Suelle would be a
condition of the contract.

If that condition is broken, naturally Selphie's contract of
servitude would also be terminated, and she would be able to
retaliate or do whatever she wants.
And most likely, what Bellra is saying is true.

If ancient spell formulas could brainwash unconditionally,
there would be no need for such roundabout methods.

"So you orchestrated Suelle and the others going to Maroges'
mansion and me coming here, all to capture me."

If that's the case, Selphie thought that quite a number of
people must be cooperating with Bellra.

Though she denies it with her words, Selphie can tell from
Bellra's attitude that her guess is correct.

And at the same time, Selphie intuitively feels that Bellra
has several other plans prepared from her composure.

Probably this is what Bellra thinks is the most effective
tactic against Selphie, but if it doesn't work, she'll
switch to another strategy.

However, in doing so, Bellra will likely carry out what she
mentioned earlier to Rise to unsettle Selphie.

This means that other than entering into a contract of
servitude, Selphie has no other way to save Suelle and the
others.
"Will you really not lay a hand on Suelle?"

"Yes, men can't just roll in money like women if they have a
body; I don't care about him in the first place."

"Actually, there's a client who's in cahoots with me this
time... They seem to want you so badly they can't stand it."

Given the meticulous planning to target Selphie, it can be
inferred that the person aiding Bellra holds considerable
power.

When Selphie tries to find out who that person is, Bellra
dismisses the question with a wave of her hand.

"Nfufu, that will be a pleasure for you to find out when you
meet them. Ever heard of confidentiality agreements?"

While giving an answer with implications, Bellra evades a
direct response by saying that if Selphie signs a contract
of servitude, she'll be trained and shipped out right away.

"Now now, you understand the situation, don't you? What will
you do, Selphie-chan?"

If Selphie is not under a contract of servitude right now,
she might be able to escape from this situation.

However, if she does so, Suelle will be dealt with by Rise,
who is one of their comrades.
Selphie could never sacrifice her comrades.

After a brief pause, Selphie agrees to the terms. But it
wasn't just to protect her comrades.

(Bellra, you're making one big mistake. If there's anyone
who can turn this situation around, it's probably Suelle.)

Even if Rise was brainwashed, even if Tina and Selphie were
brainwashed...

Selphie believed that Suelle could definitely break through
this situation, which was also why she took this action.

And so, Selphie was captured. A few hours later, Suelle and
the others would end up watching a video of Selphie.

The time rewinds to five days after Suelle shut himself
away.
